<p>Slippery elm is the ground inner bark of the slippery elm tree (ulmus fulva) discovered by the North American Indians and has been an important herb ever since. Steeped in history it is famed for its healing properties especially for stomach complaints including digestive discomfort, irritable bowel, acidity etc. To use- Mix one teaspoon in a mug of hot water, and add honey or sweetener and drink. Supplied in 40g Jar.</p>